quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  12,30,"Some city women said, ´The governor´s wife solicited her slave. He´s fired her heart with love. We see that she´s the one to blame.´"
  12,31,"But when she heard of their malicious talk, she sent for them and made a sumptuous meal and then she gave a knife to each of them. She said, ´Go out to them.´ When they saw him, they were amazed by him and cut their hands. They said, ´Allah preserve us! This is no man. What can this be but a noble angel here!´"
  12,32,"She said, ´You see! It´s him you blamed me for. I tried seducing him but he refused. If he does not do what I order him, he will be put in prison and brought low.´"
  12,33,"He said, ´My Lord, the prison is preferable to me than what they call on me to do. Unless You turn their guile away from me, it may well be that I will fall for them and so become a man of ignorance.´"
  12,34,"His Lord replied to him and turned away from him their female guile and deviousness. He is the One Who Hears, the One Who Knows"
  12,35,"Then, after they had seen the Signs, they thought that they should still imprison him for a time"
  12,36,"Two servants entered prison along with him. One said, ´I dreamt that I was pressing grapes.´ The other said, ´I dreamt I carried bread upon my head and birds were eating it. Tell us the true meaning of these dreams. We see that you´re one of the righteous.´"
  12,37,"He said, ´No meal to feed you will arrive before I have informed you what they mean. That is part of what my Lord taught me. For I have left the religion of a people who clearly have no iman in Allah and are kuffar about the world to come"
  12,38,"I hold fast to the creed of my forebears Ibrahim and Ishaq and Ya´qub. We don´t associate anything with Allah. And that is how Allah has favoured us and all mankind, but most do not give thanks"
  12,39,"My fellow-prisoners, are many lords better, or Allah, the only One, the Conqueror"
  12,40,"What you serve apart from Him are only names which you and your forefathers have made up There is no mandate for them from Allah. Allah alone is qualified to judge. His order is to worship none but Him. That is in truth the straight and upright deen, but most of mankind simply do not know"
  12,41,"My fellow-captives, one of you will serve his lord with wine, the other of you will be crucified and birds will eat his head. The thing you asked about is foreordained.´"
  12,42,"He said to the one of them he knew was saved, ´Please mention me when you are with your lord,´ but Shaytan made him forget to remind his lord, and so he stayed in prison for several years"
  12,43,"The King declared, ´I dreamt of seven fat cows which seven thin ones ate and seven green ears of wheat and seven others which were dry. O counsellors! Explain my dream to me if you are those who can interpret visions!´"
  12,44,"They said, ´A jumbled mass of mixed-up dreams! We do not know the meaning of such things.´"
  12,45,"The one of them who had been saved then said, remembering after a period, ´I will tell you what it signifies, so send me out.´"
  12,46,"´O truthful Yusuf, tell us of seven fat cows which seven thin ones ate and seven green ears of wheat and seven others which were dry so that I can return to them and let them know.´"
  12,47,"He said, ´Sow for seven years in the normal way and leave that which you harvest in the ear except for a small amount from which you eat"
  12,48,"Then after that seven hard years will arrive in which you can eat from what you set aside for them, except for a little which you store"
  12,49,Then after that another year will come in which the people will be helped by rain in plenty and when they once more will press.´
  12,50,"The King said, ´Bring him to me straight away!´ but when the envoy came to him, he said, ´Go back to your master and enquire of him what happened about the women who cut their hands. My Lord has knowledge of their cunning guile.´"
  12,51,"He said, ´What was this past affair of yours when you solicited Yusuf?´ Then they said ´Allah forbid! We know no bad of him.´ The governor´s wife then said, ´The truth has now emerged. Indeed I tried to seduce him then and he has simply told the honest truth"
  12,52,In this way he may know at last that I did not dishonour him behind his back and that Allah most surely does not guide the deviousness of the dishonourable